<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 07 at 9:20PM EDT  by NWS Raleigh</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of east central Anson
and southeastern Richmond Counties through 945 PM EDT...
At 920 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Rockingham, moving northeast at 20 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Rockingham, Hamlet, Dobbins Heights, East Rockingham and Sandhills
Game Land.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
